I missed him.

12:06.124 --> 12:08.424
I didn't... I never
dreamed he would just...

12:08.426 --> 12:10.359
show up.

12:10.361 --> 12:11.460
Is he in the car?

12:11.462 --> 12:13.463
Yup.

12:13.465 --> 12:15.364
It's not like he
came home to stay.

12:15.366 --> 12:17.934
Obviously, that can't
happen right now.

12:17.936 --> 12:19.334
It wouldn't be
good for him.

12:19.336 --> 12:20.469
He needs to go back.

12:20.471 --> 12:22.070
I agree.

12:22.072 --> 12:23.339
And if it weren't Christmas...

12:23.341 --> 12:25.340
It's the right
thing, honey.

12:25.342 --> 12:26.242
It is, Mom.

12:26.244 --> 12:28.011
We hope. We don't know.

12:28.013 --> 12:29.445
I mean, honestly...

12:29.447 --> 12:32.080
I'm so goddamn angry at
the two of you right now.

12:32.082 --> 12:33.081
I am.

12:33.083 --> 12:34.184
What did I do?

12:34.186 --> 12:35.951
You gave up on him.

12:35.953 --> 12:37.052
You both have.

12:37.054 --> 12:39.122
This is not giving up.

12:39.124 --> 12:41.424
- It is.
- It's... no, it... it's giving a shit,

12:41.426 --> 12:44.026
which we do, about
what's best for him.

12:44.028 --> 12:45.195
And for you.

12:45.197 --> 12:46.863
You have a problem
with him, Neal.

12:46.865 --> 12:49.165
No, I'm rooting for him,
but I'm frustrated.

12:49.167 --> 12:50.867
He's lucky,
and we're...

12:50.869 --> 12:52.368
- We're playing loose with it.
- OK, Neal.

12:52.370 --> 12:54.570
If he were black,
he would be in jail by now.

12:54.572 --> 12:56.138
Maybe this isn't the time.

12:56.140 --> 12:58.208
