19:08.413 --> 19:10.680
Come on.

19:10.682 --> 19:13.248
Fine. Just leave it.
We don't need anymore, Ben.

19:13.250 --> 19:14.883
Cleaning up your mess.

19:14.885 --> 19:18.286
- We'll do it. We're gonna do it.
- Aah!

19:18.288 --> 19:20.422
- It's so heavy!
- I got it. I got it.

19:20.424 --> 19:23.692
- You're good. You're good.
- Ponce!

19:23.694 --> 19:25.294
Nice. OK.

19:28.566 --> 19:30.565
We're in no danger
of it burning out.

19:30.567 --> 19:33.469
What the fuck is this?
Where did our ornaments go?

19:33.471 --> 19:35.438
They don't share
the current aesthetic.

19:35.440 --> 19:37.606
Is there a problem?

19:37.608 --> 19:41.009
Ben was just asking where
our old ornaments are.

19:41.011 --> 19:42.580
Did you throw them away?

19:50.255 --> 19:51.557
Come with me.

19:57.428 --> 19:59.996
Be quick and
be careful, yeah?

19:59.998 --> 20:02.601
- Mommy!
- Yes, yes. OK.

20:13.744 --> 20:15.479
Do you see 'em?

20:17.615 --> 20:19.651
It should be right there.

20:31.296 --> 20:33.296
Ben?

20:33.298 --> 20:34.596
Fuck!

20:34.598 --> 20:35.831
Ben?

20:35.833 --> 20:36.935
Can you come up?

20:44.041 --> 20:47.543
- That's it.
- I hate it up here.

20:47.545 --> 20:48.643
OK, then let's go already.

20:48.645 --> 20:50.379
Wait...

20:50.381 --> 20:51.883
I need you to check.

20:52.950 --> 20:54.553
I'm, uh...

20:55.920 --> 20:57.987
I used to stash
my... my, um...

20:57.989 --> 20:59.955
OK.

21:05.395 --> 21:06.731
Back there?

21:09.666 --> 21:13.638
If there's something there, then
you have to make it go away.

21:21.913 --> 21:23.414
Nothing.

21:29.386 --> 21:30.688
We're good.

21:31.955 --> 21:33.424
I'll help you down.

21:36.027 --> 21:37.696
Come on. Let's go.

21:56.713 --> 21:59.014
Oh, wow. Ben.

21:59.016 --> 22:01.816
Nice.

22:01.818 --> 22:04.056
Liam, I have
a pine cone nose.

22:05.690 --> 22:08.026
This is better.

22:09.727 --> 22:11.760
- Yeah.
- Yeah, cotton balls.

22:11.762 --> 22:14.965
Ben, Ivy, can you
two come with me, please?

22:16.601 --> 22:19.701
I know, I went a
little overboard this year.

22:19.703 --> 22:21.603
- Mom?
- Keep wrapping.

22:22.740 --> 22:23.972
Hello?

22:23.974 --> 22:25.074
- <i>Hey, honey.</i>
- <i>Yeah?</i>

22:25.076 --> 22:26.174
<i>They only have regular.</i>

22:26.176 --> 22:27.742
No.

22:27.744 --> 22:29.711
Organic cranberries.

22:29.713 --> 22:32.748
Mom, we don't
have to be 100%...

22:32.750 --> 22:34.616
It's important.

22:34.618 --> 22:35.985
- <i>Got it.</i>
- <i>OK.</i>

22:35.987 --> 22:37.018
Thank you.

22:38.855 --> 22:40.155
Ugh, gotta love that Neal.

22:40.157 --> 22:41.757
Mom?

22:41.759 --> 22:43.859
Running all my last-minute
errands so we can just...

22:43.861 --> 22:46.027
- stay here till church.
- Mom. Mom, I wanna do some shopping of my own.

22:46.029 --> 22:46.862
Why?

22:46.864 --> 22:49.064
I wanna get them
something from me.

22:49.066 --> 22:52.535
Well, sweetie,
you are the present.

22:52.537 --> 22:54.103
Something that
they can unwrap.

22:54.105 --> 22:56.639
Well, OK. Let's just say these
are from you, then.

22:56.641 --> 22:58.641
But they're not really from me.
I didn't pick them out.

22:58.643 --> 22:59.741
They'll never know.

22:59.743 --> 23:01.443
But I'll know.

23:01.445 --> 23:04.747
All right. Well, honestly,
they have everything they need.

23:04.749 --> 23:06.815
They really don't
need anything more.

23:06.817 --> 23:07.650
So true.

23:07.652 --> 23:09.184
OK, but...

23:09.186 --> 23:11.653
if I didn't pick them out,
then they're not really from me,

23:11.655 --> 23:13.122
which makes me a liar.

23:13.124 --> 23:15.024
And the whole point of this

23:15.026 --> 23:16.124
is to be honest.

23:16.126 --> 23:18.227
It's no good if
I'm not honest.

23:35.680 --> 23:37.046
This is nice.

23:37.048 --> 23:39.785
Getting to spend a little
quality alone time together.

23:45.088 --> 23:47.625
What do you think
you'll wear tonight?

23:48.526 --> 23:49.924
This is all I brought.

23:49.926 --> 23:53.629
Oh, well, no worries.
We can pick up a sweater

23:53.631 --> 23:56.701
or maybe even
a whole new ensemble.

23:57.234 --> 23:58.702
Ensemble?

24:00.171 --> 24:03.171
That way you'll... I want
you to be comfortable.

24:03.173 --> 24:04.606
Oh, I'm okay with just...

24:04.608 --> 24:06.241
No, come on.

24:06.243 --> 24:09.079
It's Christmas Eve. We're
gonna be in a front pew.

24:14.719 --> 24:16.251
Hey, Burns!

24:16.253 --> 24:17.819
What's going on?

24:17.821 --> 24:21.025
- Hey, man.
- Wow, it's been a long time.

24:21.826 --> 24:23.627
I thought you were dead.

24:25.262 --> 24:26.728
What's new?

24:26.730 --> 24:30.132
- I'm... I'm good.
- Yeah?

24:30.134 --> 24:32.634
Dude, it's... it's
really good to see you.

24:32.636 --> 24:34.536
- Yeah.
- And you look good.

24:34.538 --> 24:35.537
Oh, thank you.

24:35.539 --> 24:36.875
OK.

24:41.311 --> 24:43.879
He was a little full of
himself, don't you think?

24:43.881 --> 24:45.680
He's all right.

24:45.682 --> 24:48.017
And what's his drug of choice?
You know he has one.

24:48.019 --> 24:50.686
- Speed? Weekend cocaine?
- Mom.

24:50.688 --> 24:53.322
- High caffeinated energy drinks?
- Mom.

24:53.324 --> 24:58.227
All I'm saying is you
forget how special you are.

24:58.229 --> 24:59.795
You just don't... you don't...

24:59.797 --> 25:01.596
Well, people look up to
you, and they love you.

25:01.598 --> 25:04.866
You're a natural leader,
and you are so, so smart.

25:04.868 --> 25:06.768
No, Mom, Ivy is smart.

25:06.770 --> 25:08.770
Well, nobody wants
to be that smart.

25:08.772 --> 25:12.607
It's not like she's having a
tremendous amount of fun, hmm?

25:12.609 --> 25:13.308
What was my point?

25:13.310 --> 25:14.776
You don't have a point.

25:14.778 --> 25:15.944
I do have a point.

25:15.946 --> 25:17.813
My point is, look,
you lick this,

25:17.815 --> 25:19.815
and who knows
how far you can go

25:19.817 --> 25:21.049
and what you can do.

25:21.051 --> 25:23.187
There's so much to
look forward to.

25:34.731 --> 25:37.600
OK, honey, you've
barely touched your breakfast.

25:37.602 --> 25:40.071
You've got to eat this.
Come on now.

25:40.904 --> 25:41.903
Mrs. Crane.

25:41.905 --> 25:43.104
Dr. Crane.

25:43.106 --> 25:44.675
Oh, hello.

25:45.609 --> 25:46.810
Do I know you?

25:47.778 --> 25:49.711
Holly Burns.

25:49.713 --> 25:52.146
Yes. Oh, yes.

25:52.148 --> 25:55.249
He doesn't always remember.

25:55.251 --> 25:59.254
Holly is the mother of Ivy,
whose singing we love.

25:59.256 --> 26:01.323
She was your patient.

26:01.325 --> 26:02.991
I remember.

26:02.993 --> 26:05.760
You must
be so proud of her.

26:05.762 --> 26:08.299
I am proud of all
of my children, yes.

26:17.842 --> 26:20.345
Oh, fuck.

26:24.315 --> 26:26.315
Oh, look, I need
to get a napkin. I...

26:26.317 --> 26:27.850
I'll sit with him.

26:27.852 --> 26:29.718
You're a dear.

26:29.720 --> 26:30.822
Be right back.

26:32.789 --> 26:37.793
So, if you remember Ivy, then
you must remember my son, Ben.

26:37.795 --> 26:39.061
Right over there.

26:39.063 --> 26:40.332
Who?

26:43.366 --> 26:44.967
- I don't remember him.
- Hmm.

26:44.969 --> 26:48.036
I understand.
You had so many patients.

26:48.038 --> 26:50.271
But when was 14,
he had a small

26:50.273 --> 26:52.207
snowboarding injury.

26:52.209 --> 26:54.375
And you prescribed
painkillers.

26:54.377 --> 26:58.113
And when I asked, you told
me they weren't addictive

26:58.115 --> 27:00.282
and kept upping his dose,
and he got hooked,

27:00.284 --> 27:01.816
and it fucked up his life.

27:01.818 --> 27:03.451
So, you can pretend
you don't remember,

27:03.453 --> 27:05.720
but I won't forget.

27:05.722 --> 27:08.359
I hope you die
a horrible death.

27:11.194 --> 27:13.228
Merry Christmas.

27:13.230 --> 27:15.099
I'm just here for a day.

27:17.067 --> 27:18.199
OK. Yeah.

27:18.201 --> 27:19.703
I will.

27:20.471 --> 27:23.375
OK. Yes. I gotta go.
I gotta go.

27:24.942 --> 27:26.141
Who was that?

27:26.143 --> 27:28.142
Um, my... my sponsor.

27:28.144 --> 27:30.446
I'm feeling...
I'm feeling shaky.

27:30.448 --> 27:32.914
So, I... that's
why I called him.

27:32.916 --> 27:34.248
He told me to
go to a meeting.

27:34.250 --> 27:35.450
They all say that.

27:35.452 --> 27:38.386
Whenever you feel shaky,
get to a meeting.

27:38.388 --> 27:40.889
OK, well, let's just
get your clothes...

27:40.891 --> 27:42.894
I gotta find a meeting. Now.

27:45.863 --> 27:47.132
Did you hear me?

27:47.765 --> 27:49.797
OK.

27:49.799 --> 27:51.933
I'm so proud of you.

27:51.935 --> 27:53.134
Knowing what you need.

27:53.136 --> 27:55.304
I just, I think
it's so great.

27:55.306 --> 27:58.940
Like they say, it's
working when you...

27:58.942 --> 28:00.109
What do they say?

28:00.111 --> 28:01.209
It works if you work it.

28:01.211 --> 28:02.244
It works if you work it.

28:02.246 --> 28:03.277
Well, you are working it.

28:03.279 --> 28:04.412
Oh, let's go in.

28:04.414 --> 28:05.881
You're not coming in.

28:05.883 --> 28:07.282
No, why? Of course I am.

28:07.284 --> 28:08.750
No, Mom, I-I'm... I'm good.

28:08.752 --> 28:10.251
It's... it's a... it's a meeting.

28:10.253 --> 28:11.886
I'm gonna come right
out afterwards. No.

28:11.888 --> 28:12.787
I may just tag along.

28:12.789 --> 28:14.288
- Hi!
- Mom.

28:14.290 --> 28:15.891
- Hey, yo, what's up, baby?
- Hello.

28:15.893 --> 28:17.025
- How are you?
- Hey, how you doing?

28:17.027 --> 28:18.126
Stop.

28:18.128 --> 28:19.128
Never hurts to
be friendly.

28:19.130 --> 28:20.129
Dial it down.

28:20.131 --> 28:21.130
OK.

28:21.132 --> 28:22.296
Maybe I'll just... Hi!

28:22.298 --> 28:23.902
- Hi, guys.
- Hello.

28:25.035 --> 28:26.738
Everybody seems so nice.

28:32.509 --> 28:34.042
The minute I think I have it,

28:34.044 --> 28:37.045
the minute I think
I've got this, uh...

28:37.047 --> 28:38.479
it's waiting, you know?

28:38.481 --> 28:40.516
It's out there, doing
push-ups right now

28:40.518 --> 28:42.316
while we're sitting in
these folding chairs.

28:42.318 --> 28:45.921
So, I'm really, really grateful
to be here with all of you.

28:45.923 --> 28:48.222
And I-I thank you
for keeping me clean.

28:48.224 --> 28:50.092
Thank you for
letting me share.

28:50.094 --> 28:51.160
So, uh...

28:51.162 --> 28:53.230
Thank you.

28:55.499 --> 28:57.165
Go on to show of hands?

28:57.167 --> 28:59.934
I have a deep
fear of using.

28:59.936 --> 29:03.305
I have a deep fear of going
back into those dark places.

29:03.307 --> 29:06.007
This fellowship,
this group of people,

29:06.009 --> 29:07.809
is what keeps me alive.

29:07.811 --> 29:10.578
You know, I have two
new baby nieces,

29:10.580 --> 29:13.915
and they're going to meet
me for the first time.

29:13.917 --> 29:18.286
I'm just so grateful that
they'll never know me high.

29:18.288 --> 29:20.959
They'll just know
me as... as me.

29:22.358 --> 29:25.294
Hi, I'm Ben, and I,
um, I'm an addict.

29:25.296 --> 29:27.129
Hey, Ben.

29:27.131 --> 29:29.264
I got 77 days.

29:33.470 --> 29:36.604
And, uh, that's
my most ever.

29:36.606 --> 29:38.974
So, I just want
to get to 78...

29:38.976 --> 29:40.007
right now.

29:40.009 --> 29:42.276
Um, so, I, uh...

29:42.278 --> 29:45.046
I called my sponsor and...

29:45.048 --> 29:49.284
the thing about my sponsor is
that he's a... he's a loud talker.

29:49.286 --> 29:53.555
And, so, uh, I say,
"Hey," and he goes,

29:53.557 --> 29:55.023
"What's up?"

29:55.025 --> 29:57.058
And I was like, "Well,
I-I got big news.

29:57.060 --> 29:59.428
I just bought presents that I
actually picked out for someone."

29:59.430 --> 30:03.131
And he was like, "Oh, well,
you're feeling pretty good, huh?"

30:03.133 --> 30:06.602
And I was like, "Yeah, you know,
I actually feel like I'm being honest."

30:06.604 --> 30:09.103
And, well, he said,
"If you were honest, Ben,

30:09.105 --> 30:13.007
you'd look in the mirror and
say, I'm a great big phony."

30:13.009 --> 30:14.442
So, I was like, "OK."

30:14.444 --> 30:16.143
"Because Ben you're
a fucking addict,

30:16.145 --> 30:18.646
and you're the last person who
should believe his own bullshit.

30:18.648 --> 30:20.449
So, now get to a meeting."

30:20.451 --> 30:22.383
So, here I am.

30:22.385 --> 30:25.187
77 days clean.

30:25.189 --> 30:28.289
Some things are better now.

30:28.291 --> 30:30.191
Like I can actually
take a shit.

30:32.363 --> 30:35.197
Yeah, uh, even
better than that,

30:35.199 --> 30:38.436
I'm waking up more often
than not with an erection.

30:40.938 --> 30:41.670
Sorry, Mom.

30:41.672 --> 30:43.508
And my... yeah, my mom's here.

30:45.174 --> 30:46.476
Um...

30:48.645 --> 30:52.049
I've put her
through a lot, um...

30:53.951 --> 30:56.450
This summer, she found me
upside down on the stairs

30:56.452 --> 30:59.389
with, um, a needle in my arm.

31:00.356 --> 31:01.625
And, uh...

31:03.093 --> 31:05.928
with my dog trying
to keep me awake.

31:05.930 --> 31:07.028
So...

31:07.030 --> 31:09.498
The doctor said that if
it weren't for my dog,

31:09.500 --> 31:11.266
I... I would be dead.

31:11.268 --> 31:14.268
Um, and my mom.

31:14.270 --> 31:18.673
Without her, I wouldn't be
here right now in this room.

31:18.675 --> 31:24.446
Uh, the things that
I've done to myself

31:24.448 --> 31:25.950
and others.

31:28.652 --> 31:32.321
Uh, so, I don't...
Why am I still...

31:32.323 --> 31:34.392
here?

31:36.226 --> 31:38.259
There's gotta be a reason.

31:38.261 --> 31:39.961
Maybe it's to...

31:39.963 --> 31:42.564
come back and... and make
this Christmas right

31:42.566 --> 31:44.665
or maybe this
is the biggest

31:44.667 --> 31:47.469
fucking mistake of my life.

31:47.471 --> 31:50.505
Um, anyways,
here I am.

31:50.507 --> 31:51.640
Still here.

31:51.642 --> 31:54.178
So, thank you.
Thank you for...

31:58.715 --> 32:00.548
...grant us the serenity

32:00.550 --> 32:03.184
to accept the things
we cannot change,

32:03.186 --> 32:06.087
the courage to change
the things we can,

32:06.089 --> 32:08.457
and the wisdom to
know the difference.

32:08.459 --> 32:12.397
Keep coming back.
It works if you work it.

32:19.269 --> 32:21.402
Ben?

32:21.404 --> 32:23.671
- Ben. Good job, sweetie.
- Thanks.

32:23.673 --> 32:25.440
And you coming back
was not a mistake.

32:25.442 --> 32:29.678
Someone wiser than me, your
sponsor, said you can do this.

32:29.680 --> 32:32.546
OK.
Yeah. That's right.

32:32.548 --> 32:34.548
I think some people
want to talk to you.

32:34.550 --> 32:35.549
I'll just wait over here.

32:35.551 --> 32:37.087
OK.

32:38.422 --> 32:40.488
Hey, man.
Thanks for your share.

32:40.490 --> 32:41.789
It's been a long time, yo.

32:41.791 --> 32:45.026
- Yeah.
- That really hit home.

32:45.028 --> 32:47.432
- Thanks, man.
- Thank you.

32:52.669 --> 32:54.135
Hey.

32:54.137 --> 32:55.437
I-I loved what you said.

32:55.439 --> 32:57.104
You were... you
were very funny.

32:57.106 --> 33:00.142
There's not enough
funny around here.

33:00.144 --> 33:02.309
Thanks.

33:02.311 --> 33:04.112
- You're the mom?
- Yes.

33:04.114 --> 33:05.146
I am.

33:05.148 --> 33:06.314
It's great you
came with him.

33:06.316 --> 33:07.248
Aw, I hope so.

33:07.250 --> 33:09.383
No, my mom died before
I ever got clean.

33:09.385 --> 33:12.554
I would have given anything for
her to see me get my shit together.

33:12.556 --> 33:14.057
I'm sure.

33:18.095 --> 33:19.394
It was honest.

33:19.396 --> 33:25.734
And it was you saying it.
Someone young and hot. Oh, shit.

33:25.736 --> 33:29.438
- Oh, uh, it's... that's okay.
- Oh, I'm blushing... I'm blushing now.

33:29.440 --> 33:32.140
That makes me nervous.

33:32.142 --> 33:33.842
- Is it your first meeting?
- Uh, yeah.

33:33.844 --> 33:36.411
- I'm, you know, new to it all, so...
- Yeah?

33:36.413 --> 33:37.778
Well, you should
get a sponsor.

33:37.780 --> 33:39.680
Um, it should
be a woman.

33:39.682 --> 33:42.217
It should be someone
really tough, who will

33:42.219 --> 33:44.585
you know, call you
on your bullshit, and

33:44.587 --> 33:49.190
it's all about, you know,
rigorous honesty.

33:49.192 --> 33:50.758
Oh, they're just
talking program.

33:50.760 --> 33:53.094
It's how we help
each other.

33:53.096 --> 33:53.895
OK.

33:53.897 --> 33:55.729
So, nothing to
worry about then.

33:55.731 --> 33:58.101
Oh, I didn't say that.

34:00.503 --> 34:02.740
You don't remember, do you?

34:08.244 --> 34:09.780
You were my dealer.

34:11.248 --> 34:12.514
Oh, fuck.

34:12.516 --> 34:13.681
Oh, my. I'm sorry.

34:13.684 --> 34:16.117
No, it's fine.
I'm, uh...

34:16.119 --> 34:18.719
